org.jcvi.jillion.experimental.align.blast

Interface Hsp<R extends Residue,S extends ResidueSequence<R,S,B>,B extends ResidueSequenceBuilder<R,S>>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    SequenceAlignment<R,S>

    public interface Hsp<R extends Residue,S extends ResidueSequence<R,S,B>,B extends ResidueSequenceBuilder<R,S>>
extends SequenceAlignment<R,S>
    Hsp is an object representation of a "High-scoring Segment Pair" (HSP). HSPs are pairs of sequences whose alignments with one another meet certain scoring and statistical criteria.
    Author:
    dkatzel

      • getEvalue

        BigDecimal getEvalue()
        Get the Expectation value of this hit. The value provides a measure of statistical significance. An e-value is the probability that this hit occurred by chance. The lower the e-value, the more similar the sequences and the more confidence that this hit is homologous to the query.
        Returns:
        the e-value as a BigDecimal never null.

      • getBitScore

      • hasAlignments

        boolean hasAlignments()
        Does this Hsp contain the actual alignment information. If true then SequenceAlignment.getGappedQueryAlignment() and SequenceAlignment.getGappedSubjectAlignment() will return non-null objects.
        Returns:
        true if this Hsp does contain alignment information; false otherwise.
